<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1114515>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. a, Lampophyton spinatum n. sp. paratype, RMNH Coel. 40199 (SAF195), colony photographed in situ; b, Alcyonium dolium n. sp. holotype, RMNH Coel.40204 (SAF292); c, Leptophyton benayahui SAF289 photographed in situ; d, Leptophyton fustis n. sp., holotype, RMNH Coel. 40211 (SAF087), colony photographed in situ (T. fallax n. comb. purple morph visible in lower right corner); e, Circularius wilsoni n. comb. RMNH Coel. 40207 (SAF448), colonies growing on mussel shell photographed in situ; f, Tenerodus pollex n. gen., n. sp. holotype, RMNH Coel. 40219 (SAF420), colonies photographed in situ; g, Tenerodus fallax, n. comb. RMNH Coel. 40217 (SAF383), pink color morph; h, Tenerodus fallax, n. comb. SAF015, purple and yellow color morphs." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1114515/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1114537>
    dc:description "FIGURE7. Alcyonium dolium n. sp.holotype, RMNH Coel.40204 (SAF292).a, sclerites from collaret and points of polyp; b, tentacle sclerites; c, spindles from polyparium surface; d, clubs from polyparium surface; e, radiates from polyparium surface; f, spindle from polyparium interior; g, needles from polyparium interior, different scale; h, tuberculate spheroids from surface and interior of stalk; i, barrels from surface and interior of stalk; j, radiates from surface and interior of stalk. Scale at g applies only to sclerites at g; scale at b applies to all others." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1114537/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1114545>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Alcyonium variabile RMNH Coel. 40203 (SAF390). a, polyp sclerites; b, spindles from polyparium surface; c, needles from polyparium interior, different scale; d, clubs from surface of polyparium and stalk; e, f, radiates from surface of polyparium and stalk; g, radiates from base of stalk. Scale at c applies only to sclerites at c; scale at d applies to all others." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1114545/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1114481>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Maximum likelihood phylogeny of Octocorallia based on combined, partitioned analysis of 28S rDNA, COI and 16S mtDNA.South African species and clades are identified in blue. Filled circles indicate nodes with>70% bootstrap support and Bayesian posterior probabilities>0.95 (shown for South African clades only). Strongly supported clades (bootstrap 70%) with no South African members have been collapsed to facilitate readability. Phylogenetic position of Protodendron repens indicated with *." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1114481/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1114521>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Lampophyton planiceps RMNH Coel. 40201 (SAF239). a, sclerites from upper surface of stalk; b, tuberculate spindles and needles from base of stalk; c, details of tubercular ornamentation: top and middle, spindles of upper surface of stalk; bottom, spindles of base of stalk." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1114521/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

